    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish agriculturalist and geologist. Factor on the Ellon estate, Aberdeenshire, for many years; later took the farm of Mains, Waterton. Appointed Fordyce Lecturer on agricultural research, University of Aberdeen, 1862. Carried out notable researches on Scottish Quaternary geology and geomorphology. Fellow of the Geological Society of London, 1862.</p></note>
